rComments: This guy knows EVERYTHING about urban politics, and he's SO interested in it.
Very knowledgeable. Also the most helpful and caring prof I have ever had at the University of Toronto. He does go off on tangents but he knows a lot and always makes up for it.
Great guy, very helpful and nice. kind of boring at times, but he makes up for it. adapted and fit in very well to our class.
probably learned more relevant things from this course than any other.
he's very kind, extremely knowledgeable, dreadfully boring
Prof. Stren is easily the kindest and most accessible professor I've had at U of T.  Can stray off topic, but who cares - he's extremely knowledgeable, helpful and nice.
One word: boring! Also, he tends to go on at great lengths about Lousiville, Kentucky for no apparent reason other than his obvious appreciation for the city.
Cute little man who knows A LOT.  Very interesting to listen to, merely because he is so knowledgeable.
Some things in urban politics are oddly interesting for him :)
